# ReluctantlyAccept

    Ardan: Fine. I’ll watch your back, you watch mine. But let’s keep it simple.

    The other father nods, understanding the wariness in Ardan’s tone. On the next supply run, Ardan can count on the man to have his back, while keeping interactions minimal but effective. This cooperation builds a wary respect, but the bitterness still lingers.

    @goto GoodEnding

# AgreeToWorkTogether

    Ardan: I’ll help, but don’t think I’ve forgotten what happened. My family comes first.

    The other father nods stiffly, understanding the warning in Ardan’s tone. The bitterness remains, though both families sense the benefit of occasional cooperation.

    @goto GoodEnding

# Refuse

    Ardan: I think we’ll handle things on our own. We’ve done fine so far.

    The other father shrugs, respecting Ardan’s decision but remaining wary. Ardan’s family maintains their independence, but the tension between them and the other father’s family remains.

    @goto GoodEnding

@stop